    • getSupposedValue

      public static Object getSupposedValue​(T2LObject obj, Class cls, Executor executor)
      Tries to convert an object to a desired class. If it fails it will throw an error. Use the following to catch it. 
      
 try {
      JavaInterface.getSupposedValue(obj, cls, executor);
 } catch (T2LError e) {
      // Object cannot become of type cls
 }
      Parameters:
      obj - Object to convert
      cls - Class to covert to
      executor - Executor
      Returns:
      The object

    • getAllMethods

      public Method[] getAllMethods()
      Get all methods from object. If PARENT is not null and VALUE is Method get all methods of the parent. Otherwise return all methods in VALUE.
      Returns:
      List of methods
